entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued November 11 at 1:33PM MST by NWS Great Falls MT
entry.summary:
Light snow will develop over Beaverhead County by late this evening. The light snow will then move eastward, and move into Madison and Gallatin counties after Midnight.
Snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches are expected in the higher valleys and across the mountain passes of Southwest MT by late Tuesday morning. This includes areas around Monida Pass on Interstate 15, Bozeman Pass on Interstate 90, Ennis and West Yellowstone. For the lower elevation cities, such as Bozeman, Belgrade and Dillon snow accumulations of about a half inch to one inch are likely.
In the mountains of Southwest MT, the snow accumulations will be a bit higher, with 3 to 5 inches of snowfall likely. This would include the higher elevations around Big Sky and the Tobacco Root Mountains.
Those traveling tonight or on Tuesday morning over Monida Pass on Interstate 15, Bozeman Pass on Interstate 90, Highway 287 from Three Forks to Raynolds Pass, or Highway 191 from Gallatin Gateway to West Yellowstone should plan for areas of reduced visibility and snow covered roadways because of falling snow.
entry.cap:areaDesc: Big Belt, Bridger and Castle Mountains; Madison River Valley; Gallatin Valley; Northwest Beaverhead County; Beaverhead and Western Madison below 6000ft; Ruby Mountains and Southern Beaverhead Mountains; Gallatin and Madison County Mountains and Centennial Mountains

.PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
